Digital Pay TV, StarTimes has announced the introduction of Oscar-nominated documentaries ‘’The Cave’’ in commemoration of the 2020 International Women’s Day (IWD) and for the delight of television viewers across Africa. International Women’s Day (IWD) is celebrated on March 8 every year and the National Geographic’s brand initiative for 2020 is “Women of Impact” with focus on the movement for women’s rights. According to StarTimes, the new Oscar-nominated documentary “the cave” will commence, following history-making and bound-breaking of women whose stories create a portrait of their past, present and future impact on our world. In a statement, the company said, ‘‘The month of March will feature fantastic creatures on the National Geographic Wild while programming highlights include: Snakes in the City Season 6, Monster Constrictor, Killer Snake Island and America’s Super Snake. ‘‘The month of April will be the deadliest month ever with the most dangerous and lethal animals in the world from land, sea, and air. Programming highlights include: Predator Attack, and Crocs of The Caribbean World’s Deadliest: Lions, Predator Fail Compilation, Killer Animal Tactics and Hunter Vs Hunted. Also subscribers should Watch Out for Eyewitness: Shark Attack: Facing Jaws, Wild Peru: Fight for Life, and Dead by Dawn Compilations. ‘‘StarTimes takes credit for a vast array of documentaries channels that educate and entertain viewers and that includes; National Geographic Channel, National Geographic Wild, National Geographic Channel French, National Geographic Wild French, National Geographic Channel Portuguese, and National Geographic Wild Portuguese.’’